# Rosewarne

Rosewarne is the name of two places in Cornwall, England.
Rosewarne () is a hamlet in west Cornwall at , in the parish of Gwinear-Gwithian, near Reawla. The name of the hamlet comes from the Cornish language Roswern, containing the elements ros, meaning 'hill-spur', and gwern, meaning 'alder marsh'.
Rosewarne () is also the name of a northern area of the town of Camborne at . It gives its name to the nearby Duchy College Rosewarne, which is one of two sites of an agricultural college run by Duchy College within the Cornwall College Group.
